org.tap4j.consumer

Class TapConsumerImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tap4j.consumer.TapConsumerImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TapConsumer

    public class TapConsumerImpl
extends Object
implements TapConsumer
    Implementation of a TAP Consumer. It can use different TAP parsers. The parser can change the behaviour of the consumer, as the latter delegates the parsing and TAP model loading to the former.
    Since:
    1.0

      • load

        public TestSet load(File file)
        Parses a TAP File. Note: this method only works if the TapConsumer was constructed with an assumed character set encoding, and file really is encoded in that assumed encoding. For a more flexible approach, the caller (who should know best about the encoding of any given input file) should have already wrapped the file in an InputStreamReader, and should pass that to TapConsumer.load(Readable).
        Specified by:
        load in interface TapConsumer
        Parameters:
        file - TAP File.
        Returns:
